# Home Program – Workout Routine

---

## 1. Bird Dog with Resistance
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Sets:** 3 | **Reps:** 10

### Setup
Begin on all fours, with a resistance band looped around one hand and your opposite foot.

### Movement
Straighten your arm and opposite leg at the same time, pulling against the resistance. Hold briefly then return to the starting position and repeat.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your back straight, chin tucked, and do not let your trunk twist during the exercise.

---

## 2. Dead Bug with Swiss Ball
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Sets:** 3 | **Reps:** 10

### Setup
Begin lying on your back holding a swiss ball up against your knees, then raise your feet off the floor with your legs at a 90 degree angle.

### Movement
Slowly reach one arm overhead and straighten your opposite leg. Return to the starting position, and repeat with your opposite arm and leg.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your abdominals tight and your low back flat against the floor.

---

## 3. Standard Plank
**Frequency:** 5x Weekly  
**Sets:** 3 | **Hold:** 30 seconds  
**Note:** Add punches, rotations of the feet

### Setup
Begin lying on your front, propped up on your elbows.

### Movement
Engage your abdominal muscles and lift your hips and legs up into a plank position, keeping your elbows directly under your shoulders. Hold this position.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your back straight and maintain a gentle chin tuck during the exercise.

---

## 4. Monster Walk
**Frequency:** 1x Daily / 2x Weekly  
**Sets:** 3 | **Reps:** 10

### Instructions
With loop around ankles, step out to the right and then to the left. Repeat going back.

---

## 5. Side Plank on Elbow
**Frequency:** 5x Weekly  
**Sets:** 3 | **Hold:** 15–20 seconds

### Setup
Begin lying on your side with your feet stacked, resting on your elbow.

### Movement
Lift your hips off the floor so your body is in a straight line and your hips and shoulders are facing forward. Hold this position.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your head in line with your trunk, do not let your hips drop toward the floor, and do not roll forward or backward during the exercise.

---

## 6. Clamshell
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Sets:** 3 | **Reps:** 10

### Setup
Begin lying on your side with your knees bent and your hips and shoulders stacked.

### Movement
Engage your abdominals and raise your top knee up toward the ceiling, then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your core engaged and do not roll your hips forward or backward during the exercise.

---

## 7. Sidelying Reverse Clamshell
**Sets:** 2 | **Reps:** 10

### Setup
Begin lying on your side with your knees bent.

### Movement
Rotate your top foot upward, then lower it back to the starting position and repeat.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your knees together as you move your foot.

---

## 8. Clamshell in Abduction
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Sets:** 3 | **Reps:** 10

### Setup
Begin lying on your side with your knees bent. Lift your top leg so it is parallel with the ground.

### Movement
Slowly lift your upper knee toward the ceiling, keeping your foot in the same position. Return your leg to parallel and repeat.

### Tip
Make sure not to let your hips roll forward or backward during the exercise.

---

## 9. Wall Multifidus
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Reps:** 10 | **Hold:** 10 seconds

### Setup
Stand with back at wall and slide down wall into a slight squat.

### Movement
Gently press one elbow into wall and hold, then repeat with the other elbow.

### Tip
Keep back flat by keeping core tight.

---

## 10. Prone Press Up
**Frequency:** 2x Daily  
**Reps:** 15

### Setup
Begin lying on your stomach, with your hands by your shoulders resting flat on the ground.

### Movement
Push against the floor with your hands, bending your back upward.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your hips in contact with the floor and maintain a gentle chin tuck throughout the exercise.

---

## 11. Foam Roller Thoracic Series
**Frequency:** 2x Daily  
**Reps:** 10 per movement

### Setup
Lie lengthwise on foam roller with pillow for neck support. Perform pelvic tilt to flatten back onto roller. Arms straight up toward ceiling with palms facing in.

### Movement
1. Reach straight arms long overhead toward floor maintaining pelvic tilt, then return to starting position. Repeat 10 times.
2. Alternate straight arms in scissor motion. Repeat 10 times.
3. Make snow angel motion reaching overhead then down to hips. Repeat 10 times.

### Tip
If snow angels bother your shoulder(s), lift arms off ground more or remove that motion from the series.

---

## 12. Supine Hamstring Stretch with Doorway
**Frequency:** 2x Daily  
**Sets:** 3 | **Hold:** 30 seconds

### Setup
Begin lying on your back in a doorway with your hips next to the doorframe.

### Movement
Keeping your leg straight, raise your heel up onto the doorframe until you feel a gentle stretch in the back of your leg. Hold this position.

### Tip
Make sure to keep breathing evenly and do not lock your knee during the stretch.

---

## 13. Hip Flexor Stretch at Edge of Bed
**Frequency:** 1x Daily  
**Reps:** 3 | **Hold:** 30 seconds

### Setup
Begin lying diagonally at the edge of a table or bed, with the leg furthest from the edge bent.

### Movement
Let your straight leg hang off the edge of the bed, then pull your bent leg toward your chest and hold. You should feel a stretch in the front of the hip of your hanging leg.

### Tip
Make sure to keep your upper body relaxed and do not let your low back arch during the stretch.

